Date: Fri, 10 Jul 2026 11:50:27 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] pace: 0020 S1-slope trigger (DS4_PACE_S1_TRIGGER) -
 predictive rotate/widen on pruned-mass slope

ANCHORED TO LOCAL LIVE-TREE 2026-07-10 (post-0018 /root/ds4/ds4.c, 1314218
bytes, md5 771a39a861e9512fed2fc4528780e080); rebase needed after
pace-series canonization (the filed 0015/0016/0018 do not apply on a clean
base: the live tree carries prebreath/prefill/exchange/weighted extras, see
patches/README.md "Stato apply").

Adds the in-memory S1 pruned-mass monitor PACE was missing (live tree only
parsed DS4_PACE_S1 into s1_on, no accumulation): router probability mass on
PRUNED experts, read from the same raw-router readback as 0015 rotation,
folded per decode token into an EWMA (DS4_PACE_ALPHA_S1, default 0.10).
The absolute S1 level is measured dead; the EWMA SLOPE is the only signal
with a measured pre-collapse rise (CLAIM-011: +0.058 over ~200 tok,
0.722->0.781 local, 0.73->0.81 historical K91 => ~2.9e-4/tok).

Trigger (OFF by default, needs DS4_PACE_S1=1 + DS4_PACE_S1_TRIGGER=1):
slope over DS4_PACE_S1_SLOPE_WIN tokens (default 64, ring cap 256) must
stay >= DS4_PACE_S1_SLOPE_THR (default 0.0003/tok, from CLAIM-011) for
DS4_PACE_S1_STABLE consecutive tokens (default 16); one-window refractory
after each fire. Action DS4_PACE_S1_ACTION:
  rotate (default) - forced raw-router rotate, no cadence gate; why stays
    "rotate" so the 0018 WRAP-on-rotate policy applies unchanged; rmass is
    allocated+fed when the S1 rotate action is armed.
  widen - rides the standard sensor breath path (keep widens one step,
    breath_keep for breath_len tokens; the preceding s1_trigger JSONL event
    disambiguates it from an n-gram breath).
JSONL: ev "s1_trigger" with s1, slope, over, action; forced rotates emit
ev "rotate(s1)".

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
